layout.p:
Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 26;
                                                  written lines: 26; Uniform layout. Masorah magna occupies generally two lines in the upper and one to four lines in the lower margin of the page. The titles of the books are written on the verso of each leaf in the upper margin. A number of masoretic notes is given at the end of each books. The beginning and the end of the Hafṭarot are indicated in the margin.
